                Have you ever heard the phrase, "There aren't enough hours in the day"? It means you don't have enough time to do everything that needs to be done!

                Having too many things to do can make you feel tired and less motivated. So here are some hacks to help improve your productivity and get things done!
            </p>
            <h2>Write things down</h2>
            <p>Write down everything you need to do — this includes shopping lists, appointments, and any ideas you have.</p>
            <p>In his 2001 bestselling book <em>Getting Things Done</em>, productivity coach David Allen said you should write down your ideas on paper. But technology has changed since the book first came out, so if a pen and paper aren’t your thing, try listing your tasks on your computer or phone instead!</p>

            <h2>Cut out all distractions</h2>
            <p>Probably the biggest distraction in our modern lives is technology — especially our phones.</p>
            <p>If you find that things like turning off notifications and turning your phone face-down don’t help you stop using it, <em>The Guardian</em>’s Joel Snape recommends putting a rubber band around your phone.</p>
            <p>It’s hard to use the screen through the rubber band, and seeing or touching the rubber band will remind you that you shouldn’t be using your phone at all!</p>

            <h2>Schedule your day</h2>
            <p>Make a detailed schedule of your day, including your working hours, break times, and any personal things you have to do.</p>
            <p>When you make this schedule, pay attention to when you feel most focused and when you don’t — for example, you might not feel very focused until after lunch, or you might start to get tired near the end of the day.</p>
            <p>This will help you decide the best times to do certain tasks. Try to do easier tasks when you have less focus, and more difficult tasks when you have more focus.</p>
